OL,4,Cmore than #120 million to #651 million
OL,6,FManchester United investor and Ineos
OL,7,Ffounder Sir Jim Ratcliffe was the
OL,8,Fbiggest faller on the list, with his
OL,9,Fnet worth dropping by over #6 billion
OL,10,Fto #23.52 billion.
OL,12,FSir James Dyson was the second largest
OL,13,Ffaller, with the entrepreneur
OL,14,Fwitnessing a drop to #20.8 billion
OL,15,Ffrom #23 billion.
OL,17,FMeanwhile, Sir Richard Branson saw his
OL,18,Fwealth fall further, dropping to #2.4
OL,19,Fbillion from #4.2 billion after a
OL,20,Fchallenging year for Virgin Galactic.
